g.text: Where did you come from, Â¿babas?

g.title: j437538162
g.text: The nonsense started pretty early. Do you mean pre-Now, pre-Duviri, or Pre-Zariman?

g.title: j3044879224
g.text: You're right it did start early
But where do you FEEL like you come from

g.title: j1222575288
g.text: You're going to laugh at me... but this is the closest to a "home" as I've ever felt I've had.

g.title: j661726119
g.text: Honestly? I... don't know. The Orokin kind of erased most of Ancient Earth's records. So I have no way of knowing how far in the future exactly I'm from.

g.title: j2124612500
g.text: To feel like you come from no place and no time

g.title: j234206418
g.text: Despite what it did to you?

g.title: j1579762291
g.text: Why do you think I would laugh at you

g.title: j1196137404
g.text: My family moved a lot then I joined the army
Then with the ICR I fit in with no one and nowhere
So I understand, in a way, feeling displaced

g.title: j284953734
g.text: We don't get to pick what our homes have done to us, sometimes.

g.title: j3125658028
g.text: What it did to me, I did to myself. Just nightmares playing over and over again in my head.

g.title: j3601630363
g.text: That's... a complicated question. It has its own ghosts.

g.title: j3007341037
g.text: No, it's not abandoned. It has memories of people who call it home.

g.title: j1825832435
g.text: But I have a people and a culture I can call my own
Even if they are far away

g.title: j3604845266
g.text: SÃ­, don't I know that well
My family moved a lot then I joined the army
Then with the ICR I fit in with no one and nowhere

g.title: j1167757366
g.text: More fantasmas, more death that follows you
And I thought I knew La Flaca well

g.title: j3620048750
g.text: My other option is Duviri and... no. My history with that place is... too complicated.

g.title: j2588676346
g.text: My other option is the Zariman and it's not any kinder. It's filled with just as many ghosts and nightmares. Except there, more people than JUST me died.

g.title: j993549135
g.text: But my home has not done to me what that place has done to you, babas
I respect you for still thinking of it as where you come from

g.title: j1644467812
g.text: She's got me on speed dial.

g.title: j1473986722
g.text: Ghosts follow me wherever I go. Sometimes I wonder if I'm just a ghost myself.

g.title: j4133024765
g.text: It's the place I know the most, and the place that knows me the most, I suppose.

g.title: j1079804727
g.text: But your ghosts give me hope

g.title: j3048457706
g.text: How does my being haunted bring you hope?

g.title: j254280960
g.text: I'm glad my suffering brings you joy.

g.title: j4126446732
g.text: SÃ­, something to be said for the familiar
I suppose in time this place will feel like home for me
Mierda, I hope that is a long time

g.title: j1959866393
g.text: I see you with the other hex
I see you laughing and finding happiness
You are a fantasma, like me, like us

g.title: j2432934346
g.text: Hey. At least you have better company than I did.

g.title: j1810855431
g.text: You give me hope in that, babas

g.title: j2655466286
g.text: And I will take what little I can get

g.title: j1522105306
g.text: I... don't like you like that, I'm sorry, Lettie.

g.text: But this is not about your suffering
